Now, we can use the LIX formula:
LIX = (average number of words per sentence) × 0.4 +
      (average number of long words per 100 words) × 100

To calculate the LIX score:
- Average number of words per sentence: 20.3333 (61 / 3)
- Average number of long words per 100 words: 24.59 (15 / 61 × 100)

Now, plug the values into the LIX formula:
LIX = (20.3333) × 0.4 + (24.59) × 100 / 100
LIX = 8.13332 + 24.59
LIX ≈ 32.72

